This first iterates the list and stores the frequency of each word in the `counts` map. For this I&#39;m using the [`Map.merge`][1] method, which either associates the provided value (`1L` in this case) with the given key (`word` here) or uses the provided merge function (`Long::sum`) to combine an existent value with the given one.

Then, words with a frequency greater than `1` are removed from the map via the [`Collection.removeIf`][2] method.

The whole process has `O(n)` time complexity.


